## Installation Use Official Archive

- You can visit the official page in Go https://go.dev/dl/ for the latest version. But we use the version 1.18.1 for this Project.

```
wget https://go.dev/dl/go1.18.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz
```

- Then, Extraxt file to /usr/local/

```
sudo tar -zxvf go1.18.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz -C /usr/local/
```

- For set up the PATH environtment variable to include Go bin /usr/local/go/bin directory, can use command:

System-wide Go installation:
```
echo "export PATH=/usr/local/go/bin:${PATH}" | sudo tee /etc/profile.d/go.sh
source /etc/profile.d/go.sh
```

Spesific User Profile:
```
echo "export PATH=/usr/local/go/bin:${PATH}" | sudo tee -a $HOME/.profile
source $HOME/.profile
```

- And check version

```
go version
```
